The paper discusses incentive mechanisms for microtask crowdsourcing, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, cs.HC and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also addresses quality problems, which can be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the proposed mechanism involves worker training, which can be related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
